# DICTOGLOSS — API CONTRACTS

These are the agreed API routes. Do not create new routes without updating this document.

## ADMIN API (require role === ADMIN on every route)

| Method | Path | Purpose |
|--------|------|---------|
| POST | `/api/admin/lessons` | create lesson + sentences |
| GET | `/api/admin/lessons` | list teacher's lessons |
| GET | `/api/admin/lessons/[id]` | lesson detail + sentences + audio status |
| DELETE | `/api/admin/lessons/[id]` | soft delete |
| POST | `/api/admin/lessons/[id]/generate` | trigger audio generation for all sentences |
| GET | `/api/admin/lessons/[id]/stats` | attempt list + per-sentence accuracy |

## STUDENT API (public, no auth required)

| Method | Path | Purpose |
|--------|------|---------|
| GET | `/api/lesson/[shareToken]` | lesson metadata ONLY (title, sentence count, voice) |
| POST | `/api/lesson/[shareToken]/attempt` | create LessonAttempt, returns attemptId |
| GET | `/api/lesson/[shareToken]/audio/[sentenceId]` | presigned URL (validates playCount < 3) |
| POST | `/api/lesson/[shareToken]/answer` | submit answer; returns isCorrect + correctText if wrong |
| PATCH | `/api/lesson/[shareToken]/attempt/[id]/complete` | mark attempt as completed |

## AUTH API

| Method | Path | Purpose |
|--------|------|---------|
| POST | `/api/auth/[...nextauth]` | NextAuth handler (login only, no public registration) |

## SECURITY RULES PER ROUTE TYPE

**Admin routes**

1. `getServerSession()` — if no session → 401
2. `session.user.role === 'ADMIN'` — if not → 403
3. Zod validate body/query where applicable
4. Execute logic

**Student routes**

1. Find lesson by `shareToken` — if not found → 404
2. Zod validate body/query where applicable
3. Rate limit check
4. Execute logic
5. NEVER return `Sentence.text` in `GET /api/lesson/[shareToken]`
6. Only return `Sentence.text` in `POST .../answer` response when `isCorrect === false`

## RESPONSE FORMAT (consistent across all routes)

**Success**

```json
{ "data": { /* ... */ }, "error": null }
```

**Error**

```json
{ "data": null, "error": { "message": "string", "code": "string" } }
```

- Never expose stack traces or internal error details in `error.message`.
